Definition.WordDefinition: My \My\ (m[imac]), a. & poss. pron. [OE. mi, fr. min. See {Mine}, and cf., for loss of n, {A}, a., {An}, a.] Of or belonging to me; -- used always attributively; as, my body; my book; -- mine is used in the predicate; as, the book is mine. See {Mine}. [1913 Webster]
